<br>
<blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You don't want to spend the time getting the equipment, but you want the equipment (and access) anyway<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
Um, no. I don't want any equipment. I want to see new zones, farm trash mobs, do quests, tradeskills, etc. That was my point. And as I've said before, I'm happy to spend time doing particular things. I've farmed faction for the OT outpost, Kael/NToV, camped shards in green-con zones at level 65, etc, etc.<br>
<br>
With LDoN I get to spend a lot of time and get to see no.new.zones. Eventually, I might get a new item, but that really isn't the point.<br>
<br>
And I think you're mis-understanding my situation. We don't have 25 core raiders and 2 or 3 other guilds raiding at our times and tens of unguilded people floating about.<br>
<br>
If I zone into PoT when I get home from work I'll be lucky to see upwards of 10 people. PoK usually has less than 50.<br>
<br>
I'm part of the only guild on our server (on our team) that raids at european times.<br>
<br>
By the time I log off, those numbers have maybe doubled or tripled. But on our server we're split into 3 teams that can't even heal each other/group together let alone guild together. We've got a pretty unique perspective on low population problems. But it's only a matter of time before the problem is no longer unique to us. For the europeans that play, the effect is even more exaggerated.<br>
<br>
<blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I think it was innovative, and not that restrictive at all, it just required peeps to only get to places when they were ready/powerful enough to get there.<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
My point is that no matter how long I spend on the game, I will never be 'powerful enough' to get to those places. Ever. <br>
<br>
<blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Your complaints seem to center around the fact that you can get access to the places, but can't see the bosses,<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
Actually, my <i>comments</i> center around the complete opposite. The best thing about some PoP areas are the alternative key quests (or xp only quests). To see a zone, but not kill the boss (and consequently get the 'uber' loot).<br>
<br>
<blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> OR you can't get into a place, but could you get into VT, VP, ST?<hr></blockquote><br>
<br>
And I don't particularly think that the VT/VP/ST designs are good either. But at least they didn't form 70% of the expansion content.<br>
<br>
-<br>
<br>
I'd be fine with the idea that, for instance, if I farmed 300 mephit talons in PoN then I could hand them in for an xp only key to SolRo or PoA etc. Or 300 hero parts, or whatever.<br>
<br>
The simple fact is that without 50ish people, there is little I can do to get access to either zone.<br>
<br>
I'm happy to put in time. I can't put in people. And because of that I'm never going to see a lot of the PoP content that I'd like to.<br>
<br>
As I stated in the other post my contention is that <i>time</i> is not the only issue.<br>
<br>
PoP content is simply scales poorly. Less people = less content. Not, less effort/time = less content. No zerg = no advancement. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slaektinblood>Slaek Tinblood</A> at: 6/3/04 11:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyndaria>wyndaria</A></span><br> Posts: 251<br> <font color=#330000>(6/3/04 12:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gotta agree with Slaek</span><hr size=1> I do agree with Slaek... and, as for Idril, sheesh. <br>
