<br>
The problem you have is your server population.  I don't know how the Zeks work really, I have never had an interest in PK in any form.   I'm sorry there aren't enough peeps for you to work with. <br>
<br>
Wyndaria: If you complain that grass is blue, then proceed to explain why it's blue now when it used to be green, and I tell you it's green now and has always been green, and call your argument untrue after seeing just your statement of &quot;the grass is blue&quot;, why does that go against logic?  <br>
<br>
I read probably the first quarter to a third of the articles, and then scanned various sections of the rest of it.  So, yes I didn't read it, but what I did read is what I responded to, and why I wrote that they were untrue.  <br>
There may have been some valid points in the later parts, but their complaint/argument was based on something false.  <br>
If the base of an argument (or complaint) is untrue, then the argument itself is untrue. <br>
<br>
The basis for both articles (the portion that I read) was that PoP wasn't like the previous expansions because peeps couldn't get to certain spots/do things without huge raids and it was unfair because everyone paid the same amount of money.  Claiming that it wasn't like that in the original release, or any prior expansion (this is the grass is blue/used to be green comment).  My point is that there has always been content that is unavailable to the casual player, even in the original expansion, and places that you couldn't set foot into without potentially losing your body. (it's green now and has always been green) <br>
<br>
Yes, PoP was different, but it's also a logical progression based on the prior expansions.  Verant addressed two things.  1) the potential to lose your body as you explored and 2) that the guilds were getting huge and could just zerg rush anything and potentially win.  <br>
<br>
The graveyards were a good idea, but this also allowed for more restriction of content because the designers didn't intend for peeps just to poke around without a fear of losing their stuff.  With the graveyard, your body just popped up safe and ready to res.  So, no more casual exploration of places you haven't gotten to by going through earlier content. <br>
<br>
Addressing # 2 was damaging to the smaller guilds of peeps that actually used skill over numbers, and caused bunches of them to leave the game, including some of my long-time friends.  This was partially addressed with the option of keying (or small raids) to get to every place up to (not including) Sol Ro and the elemental planes.  However, this didn't let the small guilds kill the bosses.  The bosses were designed with the large guilds in mind.   Then again, so were the dragons in the original release.  <br>
<br>
The dragons were designed so you had to have a large pack of people to kill em.  And as the game grew, the creatures (especially bosses) had to have mudflation increases along with the PCs, or they would be too easy.  That capped in Velious where (from everything I've heard and read) it was endurance/zerg contests to kill bosses with stupidly large amounts of HPs.  Tons of peeps fighting for really long times to kill a boss.   They had to make changes to the way bosses worked, and make them different/difficult to keep peeps interested.  <br>
<br>
The adjustments we saw in luclin with several bosses in restricted areas, and the player base didn't complain (much).  They showed very willing to do the farming and killing necessary to get into the boss areas and restricted zones. <br>
<br>
Then came PoP, which was designed with the high end game in mind. It was billed as high end content, and high end content REQUIRED large organized guilds by this point.  Guilds that had shown very willing to go through tedious farming and large long battles to get to restricted content.  It was also designed with a specific linear storyline.  And yet, there were side quests that you could do to get into 2/3 of the expansion with small guilds, or you didn't want to take part in the story.  You just couldn't take full advantage of boss killing, just like the small guilds couldn't kill dragons or gods in the previous expansions before the next expansion came out.  <br>
<br>
As an aside,  if the mudflation wasn't there, then the new content wouldn't have any appeal to players.  There's no reason to move sideways, the goal of the game has always been to move up.  A perfect example of this is LoY, that was an alternative to PoP and offered raids and content that the small guilds were capable of.  It is essentially a flop because the small guilds are focused on what they can't have (Elemental access) rather than what they can have (doable raids with the potential for rather nice items).   <br>
<br>
LDoN was an effort to cater to the small guilds and casual players.   However, despite it's success, it still didn't appease them, they wanted to get to the elemental planes.  <br>
<br>
Then came GoD, which is a different effort to appease the big guilds and the small guilds at the same time.  There are raids there for various sizes, it's instanced, and it's got the single group quest progression and so on.  And of course, the loot is an increase over what was there before.  It's also a penalty to the big guilds because the raids are limited to 54 peeps rather than the 72 they had  been used to in PoP.  If it were better balanced/less buggy, it'd be a super expansion.  And yet, there are still those that complain because they can't get into the Elemental planes in PoP.  <br>
<br>
I'll try another analogy because my first one was deemed wonky. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The casual player is like a cat, and the flag requirements are a shut door.  If you are at all familiar with cats, you know that cats absolutuely positively have to be on the other side of a shut door.  However, when you open the door, they walk through, sniff a little and then go back to whatever they were doing.  If you shut the door again, they have to get through it.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=456989" target="top">Muse Idril Galelin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,   <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=860858" target="top">Exarch Mirai Tekk'sint</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reynaldofl>ReynaldoFL</A></span><br> Posts: 100<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 12:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gotta agree with Slaek</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's also a penalty to the big guilds because the raids are limited to 54 peeps rather than the 72 they had been used to in PoP.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
